RICHMOND COUNCIL TAX RISE PLANNED FOR 2018
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Faced with massive cuts in Government funding, Richmond Council
    will be raising Council Tax to protect the key services that
    residents want and need.

    Historically, under successive Governments, Richmond upon Thames
    has been poorly funded. The four year Finance Settlement arranged
    in 2016 has resulted in Richmond losing its Government General
    Grant by 2018/19. This continues to leave Richmond as the lowest
    funded Council in London with the Council Tax paid by residents
    covering an ever higher share of service costs.

